	<text xml:lang="la">
		<body>
			<div xml:id="div1" corresp="regest1">
				<p>
					<s xml:lang="la" type="auto">S[alutem] d[ico].</s>
					<s xml:lang="la" type="auto">Scio pios et studiosos tuae humanitati, domine et frater colende idemque mihi dilectissime, alias commendatos esse.</s>
					<s xml:lang="la" type="auto">Quia tamen multi errones saepe bonis viris imponunt, dum se venditant pro studiosis, cum sint nebulones, volui huic d. Gerhardo Frisio<note xml:id="fn1" type="footnote" n="1">Gerhard thom Camph. -Am 17. Juni reiste thom Camph in Begleitung von Samuel <persName ref="165">Pellikan</persName> von Zürich via St. Gallen, <placeName ref="565">Konstanz</placeName>, <placeName ref="943">Schaffhausen</placeName>, <placeName ref="97">Basel</placeName>, <placeName ref="1049">Straßburg</placeName>, <placeName ref="577">Köln</placeName>, <placeName ref="267">Deventer</placeName>, <placeName ref="8">Brabant</placeName> und <placeName ref="13">Holland</placeName> zurück in seine Heimat <placeName ref="20">Friesland</placeName>. Samuel kam am 28. September 1545 wieder zurück nach Zürich; s. <hi>Pellikan,</hi> Chronikon 171; unten <ref target="file#12270">Nr. 2223</ref>, 2-4.</note> testimonium dare fidele, ne inter errones numeretur.</s>
					<s xml:lang="la" type="auto">Est hic honesto loco et nobili familia natus, natione Frisius.</s>
					<s xml:lang="la" type="auto">Venit ad nos Tigurum pietatis et literarum ergo.</s>
					<s xml:lang="la" type="auto">Egit in aedibus d. <persName ref="165">Pellicani</persName>.</s>
					<s xml:lang="la" type="auto">Pius est et doctus.</s>
					<s xml:lang="la" type="auto">Rediturus autem domum et in patriam voluit prius videre te et ecclesiam urbemque vestram.</s>
					<s xml:lang="la" type="auto">Opulentus est.</s>
				</p>
				<p>
					<s xml:lang="la" type="auto">Subsidio non indiget.</s>
					<s xml:lang="la" type="auto">Excipe ergo illum, obsecro, uti dignus est.</s>
					<s xml:lang="la" type="auto">Hac re facies rem te dignam et mihi longe gratissimam; mire enim a nobis omnibus amatur propter pietatem, candorem et eruditionem.</s>
				</p>
				<p>
					<s xml:lang="la" type="auto">Vive et vale!</s>
				</p>
				<p>
					<s xml:lang="la" type="auto">Tiguri, 16. iunii anno 1545.</s>
				</p>
				<p>
					<s xml:lang="la" type="auto">Literas d. Laeti<note xml:id="fn2" type="footnote" n="2">Oben <ref target="file#12211">Nr. 2164</ref>.</note> tuis<note xml:id="fn3" type="footnote" n="3">Wohl mit Brief oben <ref target="file#12220">Nr. 2173</ref>, in dem allerdings nur ein Brief Hans Weisem (oben <ref target="file#12203">Nr. 2156</ref>) erwähnt ist.</note> coniunctas accepi et ago tibi gratias.</s>
					<s xml:lang="la" type="auto">Respondi d. Laeto<note xml:id="fn4" type="footnote" n="4">Nicht erhalten.</note> et d. [W]elsero<note xml:id="fnb" type="footnote" n="b">V <hi>in</hi> Vuelsero <hi>vom Verschlussband verdeckt.</hi></note><note xml:id="fn5" type="footnote" n="5">Nicht erhalten.</note>.</s>
					<s xml:lang="la" type="auto">Tulit literas <placeName ref="70">Augustam</placeName> quidam urbis [n]ostrae<note xml:id="fnc" type="footnote" n="c">n <hi>in</hi> nostrae <hi>vom Verschlussband verdeckt.</hi></note> cursor<note xml:id="fn6" type="footnote" n="6">Unbekannt.</note>.</s>
				</p>
				<p>
					<s xml:lang="la" type="auto">H. Bullingerus tuus.</s>
				</p>
				<p>
					<note type="address">[Adresse auf der Rückseite:]</note>
					<s xml:lang="la" type="auto">Praestantissimo viro d. <persName ref="19">Ambrosio Blaurero</persName>, Constantiensis ecclesiae ministro, fratri charissimo suo.</s>
					<s xml:lang="la" type="auto"><placeName ref="565">Constantz</placeName><note xml:id="fnd" type="footnote" n="d"><hi>Darunter von <persName ref="19">Blarers</persName> Hand das Empfangsdatum: 1545.</hi> 20. iumi.</note>.</s>
				</p>
			</div>
